      "repair_reason": "The remaining blockers are contributor real behavior proof and maintainer acceptance of an intentional gateway auth compatibility/security-boundary change, not a narrow code repair.; Cleared: No supply-chain or credential-exposure regression was found in the diff; the security-sensitive auth-boundary change is tracked as merge risk rather than a new security finding. (sha=073645ffe5acb7eee03ed87b0de7687335dacd5b)",
      "review_summary": "The PR narrows Gateway backend loopback auth so scoped shared-secret backend self-pairing no longer preserves self-declared operator scopes except for approval-runtime token calls, with focused tests and protocol docs updated.\n\nPR surface: Source +29, Tests +122, Docs +7. Total +158 across 11 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Current main source shows a no-Origin loopback/shared-secret backend client can skip pairing with self-declared scopes, and the linked issue describes that same source-level path.",
